  "slug": "one-nourishing-physical-act-today",
  "title": "One Nourishing Physical Act Today",
  "subtitle": "A small daily activity for when the body has been running on depletion",
  "excerpt": "A simple activity for choosing one physical act today that gives the body something rather than takes from it. For the weeks when the body has been in service mode and nothing has been given back.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A daily activity for choosing one physical thing today that nourishes rather than depletes. Not a workout, not a to-do item. One act that gives the body something it needs.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What this is",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This morning, choose one physical act that gives the body something rather than taking from it. One act. Specific. Timed or bounded. You do it today.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What counts",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "A twenty-minute walk in daylight, not as transport but as the thing itself.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "A proper breakfast sitting down, not grabbed while doing something else.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Lying flat on the floor for ten minutes with nothing required of you.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "A hot bath without a screen.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stretching for five minutes before getting out of bed.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why this works",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The body running on depletion is not fixed by large acts. A single week of daily small nourishing acts changes the pattern more reliably than one good weekend and then back to nothing. The small act matters because it is repeatable. The body registers the pattern, not the scale.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Choose one thing. Do it today. Tomorrow choose one thing again.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
